{
  "local_port": 42904,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why do I see numbers and not contacts' names? In WhatsApp?",
  "response": "If you're seeing phone numbers instead of contact names in WhatsApp, it could be due to a few reasons. Let's go through the possible causes and solutions step-by-step:\n\n1. Contacts not synced:\n   - WhatsApp relies on your phone's contact list to display names. If your contacts are not properly synced with your phone, WhatsApp will show numbers instead of names.\n   - Solution: Ensure your contacts are properly synced with your phone. Go to your phone's Contacts app and check if all your contacts are listed with names.\n\n2. WhatsApp doesn't have permission to access contacts:\n   - If WhatsApp doesn't have permission to access your phone's contacts, it won't be able to display names.\n   - Solution: Go to your phone's Settings > Apps > WhatsApp > Permissions, and make sure Contacts permission is enabled.\n\n3. Outdated WhatsApp version:\n   - An outdated version of WhatsApp might have issues displaying contact names.\n   - Solution: Update WhatsApp to the latest version from your app store.\n\n4. Corrupted WhatsApp data:\n   - Sometimes, WhatsApp's data can become corrupted, leading to display issues.\n   - Solution: Try clearing WhatsApp's cache (Settings > Apps > WhatsApp > Storage > Clear cache). If that doesn't work, you may need to uninstall and reinstall WhatsApp, making sure to back up your chats first.\n\n5. Contacts saved in a different format:\n   - If your contacts are saved with country codes or in a different format than how they appear in WhatsApp, it might not match them correctly.\n   - Solution: Ensure your contacts are saved in the same format as they appear in WhatsApp.\n\n6. New contacts not yet added to WhatsApp:\n   - If you've recently added new contacts, they might not have appeared in WhatsApp yet.\n   - Solution: Try closing and reopening WhatsApp, or restart your phone to refresh the contacts list.\n\nTo troubleshoot, start with the first solution and work your way down the list if the issue persists. If none of these solutions work, you may need to contact WhatsApp support for further assistance.\n\nRemember, always ensure you have a recent backup of your WhatsApp data before making any significant changes to the app or your phone's settings.",
